## Step 3 — What to build

**Schemas (in `src/schemas/`)**
- **User (edit):** add `publicKey: string | null` (base64 Curve25519 public key — safe to store; default `null`).
- **Conversation:** `type: 'direct' | 'group'`; `participants: ObjectId[] (ref User)` for direct; for group, **reference the existing `groupID`** and reuse Group/GroupMember for membership — do not duplicate a members list. Plus `lastMessage` ref and the project's timestamp style.
- **Message (E2EE payload only — no plaintext `content`):** `conversationId (ref)`, `senderId (ref)`, `type: 'text'|'image'`, `encryptedForReceiver: string`, `encryptedForSender: string`, `nonce: string`, `encryptionVersion: string` (default `'nacl-box-v1'`), `readBy: ObjectId[]`, timestamps.
- **Index:** compound `{ conversationId: 1, createdAt: -1 }` on Message.

**Group chat reuse:** for `type: 'group'`, derive join/send rights from existing **GroupMember** of the linked `groupID`. Reuse the existing role/permission model.

**WebSocket gateway (Socket.IO)**
- `handleConnection`: read `handshake.auth.token`, run the **shared session-verification**; on failure `client.disconnect()`; on success set `client.data.user` and register the socket in `presence.service`.
- `handleDisconnect`: remove socket; user offline only when their socket set is empty (multi-device).
- Events (validate payloads; authorize via `client.data.user`): `join-room` (verify participant/GroupMember, then join room = conversationId), `send-message` (validate → persist ciphertext → emit `new-message`; never decrypt), `typing` (broadcast `user-typing` excluding sender; not persisted), `read-receipt` (update `readBy` → emit `message-read`), and `presence` on connect/disconnect.
- Put event names + payload interfaces in `chat.events.ts`; one consistent emit shape.

**REST endpoints (POST-body style; interceptor wraps automatically)**
- `POST /api/v1/auth/keys` (JWT) — store caller's `publicKey`. Body `{ publicKey }`.
- `POST /api/v1/auth/public-key` (JWT) — fetch a user's public key. Body `{ userId }`.
- `POST /api/v1/chat/conversations` (JWT) — create direct/group. Body `{ type, participantId?, groupID? }`.
- `POST /api/v1/chat/conversations/list` (JWT) — paginated conversations. Body `{ pageNumber, itemNumber }`.
- `POST /api/v1/chat/messages` (JWT) — paginated history, ciphertext only, newest-first. Body `{ conversationID, limit, beforeMessageID? }`. **Use cursor pagination (`beforeMessageID`), not `pageNumber` offset, for messages** (offset duplicates/skips with live inserts); keep POST-body style and note the deviation. Authorize: participant (direct) or GroupMember (group). Server never decrypts.

**Design constraints:** REST history is the source of truth, the socket is live delivery only (client backfills via cursor on reconnect — support it). Every endpoint/event requires auth. Don't log ciphertext or tokens. Don't manually wrap REST responses. Keep the gateway free of any local-process assumption so a Socket.IO **Redis adapter** can be added later — but do NOT implement Redis now.

